  fiber: 20 g
  sodium: 1040 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Drain and rinse @black beans{13.4%oz}.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, beans, half the @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and half the @cumin{2%tsp}. Add 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings) and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @pork tenderloin{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with 3/4 tsp cumin (1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Rub with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp}. Place on a #baking sheet{} and roast on top rack until cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Thinly slice crosswise.

While pork roasts, pick @oregano{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; discard stems and mince leaves. Halve @orange{1} and @lime{2}. Mince @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Trim, peel, and grate @carrot{3%oz} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. In a #small bowl{}, squeeze in juice from whole orange and 1 lime half (both oranges and 1 whole lime for 4 servings). Stir in remaining cumin, remaining stock concentrates, and 1 tbsp oregano (2 tbsp for 4); set aside.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @sour cream{6%tbsp}, @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, cilantro, and as much remaining garlic as you like. Season with salt and pepper. Reserve 2 tbsp sauce (4 tbsp for 4); you'll use it in the next step. Add carrot and @shredded red cabbage{4%oz} to bowl with remaining sauce; toss to coat. Add a big squeeze of lime juice; season with salt and pepper. Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1}; thinly slice. Gently toss avocado in a second small bowl with a big squeeze of lime juice and a pinch of remaining oregano. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a small saucepan over medium-high heat. Add mojo sauce; cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted; season with pepper. Fluff rice mixture with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 tbsp for 4) and season with salt and pepper. Divide between plates with pork. Top rice mixture with reserved cilantro sauce and pork with mojo sauce. Serve with slaw, avocado salad, and any remaining lime wedges on the side.